summary: This is an internal FBI email chain from July 2019 discussing coordination for an interview with a new victim of Jeffrey Epstein at the SDNY (Southern District of New York). The emails focus on arranging victim services and maintaining rapport.

events.title: Epstein victim interview at SDNY
events.description: An interview with a new victim of Jeffrey Epstein is scheduled to take place at the Southern District of New York (SDNY). FBI victim specialists are coordinating to be present, offer services, and maintain continuity with the victim.

keyFacts: The FBI was actively coordinating victim interviews in the SDNY Epstein investigation as of July 2019.
The communication shows FBI victim specialists working to establish rapport and provide continuity of services to a new Epstein victim.
The email chain indicates coordination between multiple FBI personnel regarding victim assistance logistics.
